                    <comment id="12356625" author="mreutegg" created="Thu, 3 Nov 2005 01:41:32 +0000"  >From now on text filter implementations must be configured in the workspace.xml file. Using the service registry does not seem to work stable enough with context classloaders.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Sample configuration:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;SearchIndex class=&amp;quot;org.apache.jackrabbit.core.query.lucene.SearchIndex&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;param name=&amp;quot;path&amp;quot; value=&amp;quot;${wsp.home}/index&amp;quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;param name=&amp;quot;textFilterClasses&amp;quot; value=&amp;quot;org.apache.jackrabbit.core.query.MsExcelTextFilter,org.apache.jackrabbit.core.query.MsPowerPointTextFilter,org.apache.jackrabbit.core.query.MsWordTextFilter,org.apache.jackrabbit.core.query.PdfTextFilter&amp;quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;/SearchIndex&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Fixed in revision: 330282&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
